Photo, A Racing Buffalo? That's No Bull: Harvey Wallbanger, billed as the 
world's only racing buffalo, gets a workout with T.C. Thorstenson, his rider, 
trainer and owner. Harvey will be featured in an exhibition race against two 
quarter horses about 9 tonight -- between the fifth and sixth races -- at Los 
Alamitos Race Course. Thorstenson and his 9-year-old bison have performed in 
exhibition races throughout the United States, Canada and Mexico. Thorstenson 
says, "Buffalo are naturally speedy creatures"; nevertheless, he rides Harvey 
every day to keep him in shape. "I sometimes wonder," he adds, "if he thinks 
he's a horse." ; Photo, ROBERT LACHMAN / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
