ONE FAN WON'T FORGET COMMENTS BY PAGLIARULO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If in fact the criticism was aimed at Tony Gwynn, I think Mike Pagliarulo has a 
lot of audacity. 
</P>
<P>
Tony Gwynn is the Padres. He comes to play every game. The same cannot be said 
of his teammates. If they would follow his example of fighting for batting cage 
time and not going out for drinks after games instead of criticizing him, this 
team would stand a chance of achieving its potential. 
</P>
<P>
If it's true that the Yankees have asked one of their players to give up the 
No. 13, perhaps Jack McKeon would agree to let Pagliarulo go back to New York 
and reclaim it. 
</P>
<P>
LINDA ADAMS, Leucadia 
