<HEADLINE>
<P>
KEETER EDGES BRADER TO WIN VENTURA MAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Don Keeter of Ventura and Lynn Brader of Somis exchanged leads frequently in 
the 15-lap Street Stock main event at Ventura Raceway on Friday night before 
Keeter held on to win by a half-car length. 
</P>
<P>
After two re-starts and numerous yellow flags, Brader and Keeter launched their 
duel. 
</P>
<P>
Brader held the lead through eight laps before Keeter took the lead on Lap 9 
when Brader went high in Turn 2. Brader powered ahead in the front straightaway 
on Lap 10, however. Brader went high again in Turn 2 on the final lap, allowing 
Keeter to take a slight lead before both cars bumped and slid in Turn 4, with 
Keeter nosing out Brader at the finish line for his third main-event win of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
Mini Stock figure-eight season points leader Richard Webster of Camarillo and 
Cory Kruseman of Ventura battled the entire way for the checkered flag in the 
10-lap main event. 
</P>
<P>
Kruseman had just edged past Webster on Lap 7 when a yellow flag came out, 
allowing Webster to go back in front and hold off Kruseman for the victory. 
Randy Bingham of Camarillo was third. 
</P>
<P>
Scott Olsen of Ventura improved his fifth-place season points standing in the 
Street Stock figure-eight division, driving to his first main-event win of the 
season in the eight-lap race. Jim Firsich of Port Hueneme and Larry Lucies of 
Point Mugu finished second and third, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
Mini Stock eight-lap heat-race winners were Bingham, Pat Garrety of Ventura, 
and Marty Desbrow of Ventura. 
</P>
</TEXT>
