</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dirk Minniefield, a former NBA player whose career was cut short because of 
drug abuse, was jailed in Lexington, Ky., for allegedly writing bad checks. 
</P>
<P>
He was jailed after he failed to appear at a hearing on 30 charges of writing 
bad checks and one charge of shoplifting. One of the charges -- a bad check 
written for $641.06 -- is a felony; the others are misdemeanors. 
</P>
<P>
Minniefield faces a possible penalty of one to five years imprisonment on the 
felony charge. The misdemeanor charges could lead to confinement for up to one 
year. 
</P>
<P>
Minniefield played for the Cleveland Cavaliers, the Houston Rockets and the the 
Boston Celtics before being admitted to a drug rehabilitation center in 1988. 
</P>
