<P>
SEX AND SINGING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Why, in his positive review of the Lisa Stansfield concert (May 26), does Chris 
Willman include the comments she "can't dance to save her life" and she doesn't 
have "overwhelming" sex appeal. 
</P>
<P>
Stansfield's performance isn't built around dancing -- so what? She chose a 
neutral outfit that doesn't distract from her explosive vocal performance -- so 
what? Such comments only serve to perpetuate the destructive cliche -- 
engendered by MTV -- that a female singer must wrap her talent in cheap 
sexuality and innuendo. 
</P>
<P>
BARBARA L. GALLEN 
