REACTION TO ANTIVIVISECTION 'ADVER-TORIAL' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The media have been notoriously pro-vivisection, because the powers that be 
want it that way. 
</P>
<P>
Big business rides on funds for animal research. The chemical companies and 
their sister pharmaceutical companies, together with manufacturers that test 
products on animals, sponsor many of our television shows and place costly ads 
in newspapers. 
</P>
<P>
I was amazed at The Times' unbiased portrayal of this long-overdue commercial 
and the SUPRESS organization in general. 
