<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ON WEEKEND TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With local basketball and hockey long done, baseball highlights the sports 
choices on TV this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
Crucial is usually not an appropriate label to a series scheduled for the first 
week of June. 
</P>
<P>
But that designation does apply to the Dodgers-Cincinnati Reds matchup as the 
locals desperately seek to remain a credible pennant contender. SportsChannel 
will televise tonight's game at 7. 
</P>
<P>
The Angels, no longer underachievers but overachievers, meet the Texas Rangers 
at 5:30 p.m. today on KTLA Channel 5. 
</P>
<P>
Finally beginning to meet their lofty preseason expectations, the San Diego 
Padres play host to the Atlanta Braves tonight at 7 (TBS and San Diego Cable 
Sports) and 1 p.m. Sunday on TBS. 
</P>
<P>
Two area college baseball teams will also make television appearances today. 
Cal State Fullerton faces Oklahoma State at 5 p.m. on ESPN. Cal State 
Northridge goes for the Division II championship against Jacksonville (Ala.) 
State. Prime Ticket will have delayed coverage beginning at 5:30 p.m. STEVEN 
HERBERT 
