<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN SHOOTS GRANDFATHER TO DEATH, THEN 
HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Eagle Rock man on Thursday was shot and killed by his step-grandson, who 
then shot himself to death, police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
James Penuela, 18, shot Euiogio Ayala, 65, apparently once in the head with a 
semi-automatic rifle, then shot himself in the head, said Detective Grover 
Randolph of the Northeast Division. Penuela's 10-year-old sister, who lived at 
Ayala's apartment in the 4600 block of Eagle Rock Boulevard, discovered the 
bodies when she came home from school, Randolph said. 
</P>
<P>
The youth apparently was angry about a dispute between the families of his 
mother and stepfather, who are divorced, the detective said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
