<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CONSTRUCTION WORKER SHOT TO DEATH ON SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A construction worker was shot to death Friday in the yard of a Rowland Heights 
home, allegedly by a man who was upset because the victim would not give him a 
ride, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, a 23-year-old City of Industry man, was shot once in the head as he 
worked in the side yard of the home in the 17900 block of Sunrise Drive. 
</P>
<P>
He was not identified pending notification of his family. 
</P>
<P>
Other construction workers witnessed the shooting, said Sgt. Joaquin Herran of 
the sheriff's Information Bureau. Authorities believe the suspect, whose 
identity was not determined, had argued with the victim about a ride on 
Thursday. The suspect drove away after the shooting and had not been found, 
Herran said. 
</P>
