VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OAK VIEW; 
</P>
<P>
MAN ESCAPES THIEVES BY JUMPING ON CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 32-year-old man said he was kidnaped and robbed alongside a road in Oak View 
Thursday night but escaped by jumping onto the hood of a passing car, 
authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Bersach, 32, of Glendale said he was riding from San Luis Obispo to 
Glendale with two acquaintances about 10:30 p.m. when they told him that they 
were going to beat and rob him, Ventura County Sheriff's Department Lt. Joe 
Funchess said. 
</P>
<P>
The two men drove onto California 33 from the Ventura Freeway and parked next 
to the highway. They took Bersach's wallet and began beating him, Funchess 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Bersach jumped onto the hood of a car and was taken to a service station, where 
sheriff's officers were called, Funchess said. He was treated for head injuries 
at the Ojai Valley Community Hospital. The assailants were still at large. 
CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
