TEEN-AGER ARRESTED IN SQUIRT GUN SCARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Simi Valley teen-ager was arrested Friday after waving a plastic Uzi squirt 
gun at motorists on the Ventura Freeway, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Jess Paul Brown, 18, was being held Friday in the Ventura Jail on suspicion of 
brandishing a firearm on the highway, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
The CHP received two separate reports about 8 a.m. of a man waving a gun. 
</P>
<P>
At 12:40 p.m., a commuter flagged down a CHP officer patrolling the Conejo 
Grade area and said a man in a car had just pointed an Uzi at him. 
</P>
<P>
As they talked, the car and driver that the commuter had described passed them, 
the CHP said. The officer pulled the car over and found the squirt gun. 
</P>
<P>
He arrested Brown, who matched the description given by two motorists. 
</P>
