<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY OVER BART SIMPSON T-SHIRTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This letter is in response to Randy Lewis's article about Bart Simpson and the 
T-shirt controversy. ("Let's Give the Kids a Break on the Bart Simpson 
T-Shirts, OK?" May 13.) 
</P>
<P>
A break! . . . I realize it's just one thing. By itself it appears to be 
perfectly harmless. But added to the TV shows offered today, the drug 
availability, the push towards having bigger and better things, the decline in 
church attendance, the breakdown of our families (due in part to working moms 
-- for whatever reason), the increased divorce rate, single-parent homes and 
the shared custody of children, the gradual increase in acceptability of 
homosexuality, the increase in violent crime, the increase in child abuse . . . 
the list goes on. 
</P>
<P>
My point is, I can't accept one more "little thing" because it is affecting the 
moral fiber of the country. It is destroying our lives. Think about the little 
things. They eventually grow into big things if you let them. 
</P>
<P>
TERRY J. MCGRAIL 
</P>
<P>
Yorba Linda 
</P>
</TEXT>
