<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTH FOR CHRIST HEADQUARTERS LEAVING ILLINOIS FOR COLORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Youth for Christ, an evangelical organization that had Billy Graham as one of 
its first employees, has announced that it is moving its national headquarters 
to Colorado Springs, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
Its headquarters had been in Wheaton and Carol Stream, Ill., in suburban 
Chicago, which has been called the nation's evangelical capital because of the 
many Christian groups based there. 
</P>
<P>
Youth for Christ has 235 chapters around the country, 900 staff persons and 
8,000 volunteers. 
</P>
<P>
Officials of the organization said that Dallas, Indianapolis and Orlando, Fla., 
were also considered for the new headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
Reasons for the move included lower costs and a desire to develop "more of our 
own identity" by relocating "out of an area where there are so many Christian 
organizations." 
</P>
<P>
Another large organization, Campus Crusade for Christ, last year announced that 
it will move its headquarters from San Bernardino to Orlando. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA060290-0115 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 227884 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 2, 1990, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
