<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHILDREN IN FOSTER CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Kathie Bozanich and Janice L. Jones / Los Angeles 
Times, Graphics by Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The number of children in Orange County foster care homes has been steadily 
rising during the last three years, rising 14.4% between 1987 and 1989. The 
bulk of that increase, 11%, occurred between 1987 and 1988. At the same time, 
the average age has been decreasing. Here's a profile of foster care children 
in the county during the last three years. The gender, ethnicity and type of 
home categories are reported in percentages, which, because of rounding, may 
not add up to 100%: 
</P>
