<P>
</P>
<P>
* Group homes are county-licensed shelters with paid staff. They are a common 
option for emotionally disturbed children who cannot function in a traditional 
family setting. Maximum age for a foster child in any type of home is 18 or 
until high school graduation. 
</P>
