<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rising in the Ranks: Newport Pacific Development Corp. has broken into the top 
rank of apartment builders nationally, placing 10th on Builder Magazine's most 
recent list, for 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Pacific started 1,998 apartment units last year. 
</P>
<P>
That, combined with 49 single family units the company began, also earned the 
firm the magazine's ranking as the country's 34th largest residential builder 
overall. 
</P>
<P>
Many local builders are heading for Riverside, San Bernardino and San Diego 
counties to do their thing, but Newport Pacific Chairman Magdy Hanna said his 
company did 95% of its work in Orange County last year. Not only that, but, 
eschewing the fashionable South County, Newport did most of its work -- 66% of 
all the units it started -- in Anaheim. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
